                <h1>Pros and Cons of Background Checks: What You Need to Know</h1>
                <p>Background checks can enhance safety by identifying potential risks associated with hiring or renting. They promote trust but may invade privacy and lead to discrimination if misused. Furthermore, the process can cause delays and be costly. Weighing these pros and cons is essential to ensure fair outcomes for all parties involved.</p>
